2. User’s Information
2.1. User’s Information in this Policy shall be understood as the information that is associated with a certain User, both provided by User himself and gathered automatically by Persona Game Studio, although such User may not be identifiable and all the information constitutes anonymized data.
2.2. Persona Game Studio processes information that the User provides himself by filling in the relevant forms in the Application, including filling in User’s profile (e.g. nickname), subscribing to a newsletter, contact information (such as name and email address), approaching Persona Game Studio for technical support or using the feedback form, taking part in promotions and community competitions, messages and other content the User submits using the Application (such as chat logs and player support tickets), etc. Persona Game Studio can set requirements to the content of the information that is mandatory to be provided in order for the User to do certain actions. If Persona Game Studio hasn’t marked the information as mandatory the User provides or discloses such information at his own discretion.
2.3. When logging in to the Application with the services of authentication (like Facebook, VKontakte, Odnoklassniki, Apple's Game Center, Open ID, etc), these services provide Persona Game Studio with the following information about the User: User’s name and User’s identification number in this authentication system.
2.4. Besides, Persona Game Studio creates a unique identifier of each User (a player’s identifier). The player’s identifier is linked to the information of the User’s profile.
2.5. Persona Game Studio collects the data on the User’s interaction with a game and other players inside the game via server, Application, or game log files. Such information can be linked to the player’s identifier.
2.6. When you use the Applications Persona Game Studio automatically collects the following anonymized data: the unique identifier of the device (persistent or non-persistent), Medium Access Control address (MAC-address), International Mobile Equipment Identity (IMEI), name, model and other information about the mobile device, IP-address, information about communication network, approximate location (country, region, city), information about the operation system, information about time and frequency of the visits, statistics of use of the Application and Advertising ID.
2.7. In case the information provided by you contains personal data you with your own free will and for your benefit give written consent to any method of their processing including any action (operation) or a combination of actions (operations) made with the help of the automation solutions or without the help of such solutions with personal data including collection, recording, systematization, accumulation, storage, clarification (update, change), extraction, use, transfer (distribution, submission, access) to the third parties including cross-border transfer to the territory of foreign states, anonymization, blocking, deletion, destruction of personal data within the purposes stipulated by this Policy.
2.8. The legal basis on which Persona Game Studio relies for the use of User’s information includes:
2.8.1. Processing of User’s information where User has given consent for one or more specific purposes;
2.8.2. Processing of User’s information that is necessary for performing a contract to which User are party;
2.8.3. Processing of User’s information that is necessary to take steps at User’s request prior to entering into a contract;
2.8.4. Processing of User’s information that is necessary for Persona Game Studio to comply with a legal obligation.
